rComments: Professor Kempf is engaging, compelling, and authentic.   His practice clearly draws on a deep well of life experience. He is unafraid of ambiguity and skilfully foments independent critical thought.   I have now had 10 instructors at OISE. Some have disappointed me. More have bored me. A few have deeply engaged me. Arlo has inspired me.

Taking Professor Kempf's class was not only a pleasure but a life changing experience. Every lecture was though provoking, original and well organized. His views on equity and  diversity both in the classroom and in Canadian society were vital building blocks in allowing myself to internalize my own beliefs and thoughts related to the subjectmatter
His assignments were challenging but useful. I was actually excited to wake up for 830 classes to attend his lectures. Great Prof and a really nice guy!
An inspirational man and exceptionally effective educator. The bar to which all other profs will be measured against. He is the teacher I will remember years from now.
he's the one that changes the game for students.
